LONDON (AP) — England was reduced to 14 men against Ireland early in their key Six Nations rugby match on Saturday at Twickenham when lock Charlie Ewels was sent off.Ewels collided head on into Irish counterpart James Ryan’s head after Ryan had just offloaded.Referee Mathieu Raynal easily decided the tackle was dangerous and high and, after only 82 seconds, red-carded Ewels.Ryan left the field and failed a head injury assessment, and was replaced permanently by Iain Henderson.England and Ireland had to win their encounter to stay in the title race.___More AP rugby: https://apnews.com/hub/rugby and https://twitter.com/AP_Sports